FT  14 DEC 94 / International Company News: Life insurer pays Dollars 300m
for Delaware
Lincoln National, the US life insurance and financial services group based
in Fort Wayne, Indiana, is paying about Dollars 300m for Delaware Management
Holdings, which has Dollars 25bn under management.
It will also take on Dollars 209m of the company's debt.
The deal is a further sign of consolidation in the US investment management
industry.
With Delaware's Dollars 16bn of institutional assets and Dollars 9bn of
mutual funds, the enlarged Lincoln will have a total of Dollars 60bn under
management. Delaware also manages Dollars 2.2bn of international bond and
equity assets in London.
